title={Discussing the Impact of Industry 4.0 in Agriculture Supply Chain},
journal={Lecture Notes in Mechanical Engineering},
year={2021},
pages={301-307},
doi={10.1007/978-981-16-3033-0_28},
note={cited By 0; Conference of International Conference on Evolution in Manufacturing, ICEM 2020 ; Conference Date: 10 December 2020 Through 12 December 2020;  Conference Code:263049},
url={https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85113359172&doi=10.1007%2f978-981-16-3033-0_28&partnerID=40&md5=600ceccf0508767a5e0aaa3224a94f18},
affiliation={GITAM Institute of Management, GITAM (Deemed To Be University), Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, India; Department of Management, Birla Institute of Technology Mesra, Ranchi, Jharkhand, India; Department of Industrial and Production Engineering, Guru Ghashidas Vishwavidyalaya (A Central University), Bilaspur, Chhatisgarh, India; University School of Business, Chandigarh University, Mohali, Punjab, India},
abstract={Industry 4.0 is about digitization and incorporating monitoring, tracking, and analyzing analytics technologies to supply chain management and improving operational proficiency and efficiency. Industry 4.0 empowers the assembling part to become digitalized by using sensors and other electronic devices for all intents and purposes in all assembling segments, items, and gear. This paper discusses the impact of industry 4.0 to agriculture supply chain. A thorough literature review was done in industry 4.0, and how it can be applied to the agriculture supply chain. The study was mainly done through secondary data, including research papers, articles, and journals published. The findings indicate that the digitization of the agriculture supply chain industry can yield several benefits in many agriculture supply chain functions. It also shows how efficiency, productivity, and customer satisfaction can be met through industry 4.0 in agriculture supply chain management. This paper can be used to foresee the future collaboration of industry 4.0 and agriculture supply chain management which will lead to industry 4.0 to agriculture 4.0. © 2021, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd.},
